1.Create SNS Topic
  Go to SNS → Topics → Create topic
  Type: Standard
  Name: monitoring-alerts
  Create the topic.
2.Subscribe Email to Topic
  In the topic → Create subscription
  Protocol: Email
  Endpoint: your email
  Confirm subscription from your email inbox.
3.Create CloudWatch Alarm for EC2 (example)
  Go to CloudWatch → Alarms → All alarms → Create alarm
  Click Select metric
  Choose: EC2 → Per-Instance Metrics → CPUUtilization
  Pick an instance → Select metric.
  Set conditions (example):
      Threshold: >= 80%
      Period: 5 minutes
  In Notification section:
      Alarm state: In alarm
      Send to SNS topic: monitoring-alerts
  Name alarm: high-cpu-ec2
  Create alarm.
4.Create Billing / Cost Alert (simple way)
  Go to Billing → Budgets → Create budget
  Type: Cost budget
  Set monthly limit (e.g. $10)
  Configure email notifications to your address
  Save budget.
5.Test Alarm
  Temporarily lower CPU threshold or stress instance
  Wait for alarm to go into ALARM state
  Confirm email notification arrives.
